Gastroenterology is the component of the 4th year internal medicine curriculum. Gastroenterology curriculum will provide students  theoretical knowledge of gastrointestinal and hepatobiliary diseases.The theoretical knowledge will be fortified by real life patients cases.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The purpose of the gastroenterology curriculum is to  provide the basic competency and  knowledge  of gastrointestinal and hepatobiliary diseases - etiology, pathogenesis, diagnosis, differential diagnosis and main principles of management.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  The students will be able to: 1) have theoretical knowledge - prevalence, etiology, diagnosis, treatment - of gastrointestinal and hepatobiliary diseases; 2) carry out a complete history and physical examination emphasizing the gastrointestinal system; 3) outline a diagnostic impression and a short differential diagnosis of gastrointestinal and hepatobiliary diseases; 4) suggest treatment and management of gastrointestinal and hepatobiliary diseases.
